It is probably fair to say that there is a shortage of topclass referees involved in Super Rugby across the board and that has been the case for a couple of years now, but the so-called study coming out of Australia and accusing South African officials of grossly favouring their own teams in matches played over here is a very superficial analysis. In fact, it is obviously a desperate attempt to try and divert attention from the parlous state Australian rugby finds itself in at the moment. Not only have they hardly been a hotbed for good referees for many...